name: SRMR - Provisional Race Route
description:
This is the first version of the Race Route that is ready to be shared.  The overall route has already had GPS data from the ground added to correct variations where the map doesn't match roads and tracks on the ground, this will not change unless there are major changes in conditions on the ground that we become aware of.

There may be slight changes to the following:

- Exact location of the Checkpoints (a question of meters rather than kilometers)

- Exact route out of Bishkek. There is a high probability that we will be getting a police escort and possible road closures so this could affect our route out of town but this remains to be confirmed

- Exact location of the finish line and party

points_of_interest.name: Difficult Terrain
points_of_interest.description: Shamshy pass is essentially a horse track. There are around 20 kilometers of the route here which will most likely require dismounting from your bike. The descent from the pass is extremely steep on loose terrain, proceed with caution.

points_of_interest.name: Border Checkpoint
points_of_interest.description: Ride past the checkpoint following the route. You should not need to go and see the border guards.

points_of_interest.name: Military Checkpoint
points_of_interest.description: Your Border Zone Permit will be checked as you leave the border zone with China.

points_of_interest.name: River Crossing
points_of_interest.description: This river crossing is a little more serious than any others.  Depending on the time of day the water level can vary quite a lot. It can be around thigh, almost waist deep in spots. Carefully chose the exact path to cross. Don't underestimate the power of the flow. The best time to cross is the early morning.

points_of_interest.name: Construction
points_of_interest.description: From KM325.5 to KM367 there is a new highway under construction by the Chinese. The surface was partially complete at the time of scouting. Presence of construction equipment and trucks. Be particularly careful during this section of the race.

points_of_interest.name: Steep incline & fencing remains
points_of_interest.description: This section of the route used to be a military access road in a zone that was much more tightly controlled in soviet times because of the proximity with China. Much of this section of road follows old barbed wire fences. There is still barbed wire strewn on the floor in places. Caution.

points_of_interest.name: Main road to China
points_of_interest.description: When we were there traffic was very low but the surface is good (fast) and there are trucks traveling to and from China.

points_of_interest.name: Shipping Containers
points_of_interest.description: There are two shipping containers here. One is clearly used by sheep and full of dung. The other you can just about squeeze in and is relatively clean. Two cosy nights were spent here during scouting. No guarantee that they're still there, but it's likely that they are.
